1
00:01:32,599 --> 00:01:33,480
That reckless boy.

2
00:01:34,760 --> 00:01:36,680
We tried every way to clear his name,

3
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:37,280
and what does he do?

4
00:01:37,480 --> 00:01:38,879
He had evidence and didn't show it sooner!

5
00:01:39,799 --> 00:01:40,239
What?

6
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:41,680
Doesn't he trust Us?

7
00:01:44,439 --> 00:01:45,280
Laugh, laugh, laugh.

8
00:01:45,599 --> 00:01:47,040
He trusts you most, alright?

9
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:49,879
Shipeng.

10
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:50,480
Your Majesty.

11
00:01:51,159 --> 00:01:52,799
Send men to Zhenyuan County

12
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:55,159
to find the evidence Ning Chen mentioned.

13
00:01:55,519 --> 00:01:56,879
Verify whether it's authentic.

14
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:57,799
If confirmed,

15
00:01:57,920 --> 00:02:00,040
arrest every official in Chongzhou,

16
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:02,120
and bring them to the capital for trial.

17
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:04,760
If anyone resists or obstructs,

18
00:02:05,359 --> 00:02:06,599
execute them on the spot.

19
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:07,200
Yes.

20
00:02:08,719 --> 00:02:09,439
Old General Chen.

21
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:11,479
The poem that boy wrote in the prison cart,

22
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:12,639
have you heard of it?

23
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:13,879
A poem?

24
00:02:15,319 --> 00:02:16,319
Listen carefully.

25
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:18,319
We shall recite it for you.

26
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:21,960
A thousand strikes carved it from the mountain deep,

27
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:24,479
Through raging fires it stands unflinching.

28
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:27,120
Though crushed to dust, it bears no fear at all,

29
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:30,520
To leave its purity upon this world.

30
00:02:32,759 --> 00:02:34,360
Listen to that! Look at this!

31
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:36,560
If he weren't an immortal reborn,

32
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:38,319
how could he, at his age,

33
00:02:38,479 --> 00:02:40,439
possess such brilliant talent?

34
00:02:40,599 --> 00:02:42,520
Send people to spread these poems,

35
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:45,120
but don't reveal who wrote them yet.

36
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:45,879
Yes.

37
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:48,719
Oh, by the way,

38
00:02:50,039 --> 00:02:52,159
did the Crown Prince plead for Ning Chen?

39
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:55,000
The Crown Prince said not a word.

40
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:57,039
Such a fool.

41
00:02:57,919 --> 00:03:00,360
This was the perfect moment to win hearts.

42
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:01,560
Truly,

43
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,000
he really worries Us to death.

44
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:03,759
Look,

45
00:03:04,199 --> 00:03:06,680
even Huai'an knew to plead for Ning Chen.

46
00:03:08,439 --> 00:03:11,360
Why did Huai'an suddenly plead for Ning Chen?

47
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:15,240
Could it be the Ninth Princess didn't want

48
00:03:15,599 --> 00:03:20,039
a young talent like Lord Ning to be executed?

49
00:03:20,919 --> 00:03:25,280
It would truly be a loss for our Daxuan.

50
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,319
No way.

51
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:29,039
I know that silly girl too well.

52
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:30,719
She couldn't possibly think that deeply.

53
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,080
Counting the years,

54
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:35,919
Princess Huai'an must be nearly 18 now.

55
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,080
Could it be...

56
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:53,599
Your Highness, we've reached the capital.

57
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:56,199
Your Highness.

58
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:57,560
Finally back in the capital.

59
00:03:57,919 --> 00:03:59,960
Stuck in the Weilong Army camp every day,

60
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:01,319
it was so dreadfully dull.

61
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:02,680
Once we return to the manor,

62
00:04:02,879 --> 00:04:03,759
you two

63
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:07,120
must help relieve my fatigue properly.

64
00:04:07,599 --> 00:04:08,719
Your Highness, rest assured.

65
00:04:09,919 --> 00:04:12,039
We shall serve you well.

66
00:04:13,319 --> 00:04:14,159
Good.

67
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:16,720
Your Highness, something big has happened!

68
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:17,959
Imperial Inspectorate Silver Robe Ning Chen

69
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:19,439
beheaded the Imperial Uncle in Zhenyuan County.

70
00:04:19,759 --> 00:04:21,720
The Empress has fainted from weeping several times.

71
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:22,839
What?

72
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:25,240
Where is that what's-his-name Chen?

73
00:04:25,759 --> 00:04:26,959
In the Imperial Inspectorate's dungeon.

74
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:28,160
To the Imperial Inspectorate!

75
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:32,079
Remember to wake me up tomorrow morning!

76
00:04:46,639 --> 00:04:47,600
So you're Ning Chen.

77
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,399
He's not here on friendly terms.

78
00:04:55,959 --> 00:04:57,399
I'm talking to you. Are you mute?

79
00:04:59,360 --> 00:04:59,920
No, I'm not.

80
00:05:00,319 --> 00:05:01,000
My name is Ning Gan.

81
00:05:02,759 --> 00:05:03,480
Ning Gan, huh?

82
00:05:05,199 --> 00:05:05,720
Your Highness.

83
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:07,560
He is Ning Chen.

84
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:08,439
How dare you!

85
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:11,199
You dare deceive me at death's door!

86
00:05:11,879 --> 00:05:12,839
Striking down the Imperial Uncle,

87
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:14,079
defying the dignity of the royal house.

88
00:05:14,439 --> 00:05:16,480
Today, you shall pay in blood.

89
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:17,480
Your Highness.

90
00:05:18,279 --> 00:05:20,920
This guy's a prince?

91
00:05:21,319 --> 00:05:21,920
Open the door.

92
00:05:22,079 --> 00:05:22,480
Yes.

93
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:32,560
Your Highness,

94
00:05:33,279 --> 00:05:34,279
I must remind you,

95
00:05:34,879 --> 00:05:36,240
this is the Imperial Inspectorate.

96
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,199
Are you sure you want to do this here?

97
00:05:39,439 --> 00:05:41,079
What of the Imperial Inspectorate?

98
00:05:41,399 --> 00:05:42,879
If I kill a lowly Silver Robe like you,

99
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:44,560
would Father really execute me?

100
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:46,759
You killed my uncle,

101
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:49,160
leaving my mother in tears every day.

102
00:05:49,839 --> 00:05:50,879
If I don't kill you today,

103
00:05:51,639 --> 00:05:52,680
I'd be unworthy as a son.

104
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:54,600
Today, I'll use your head

105
00:05:55,199 --> 00:05:57,399
to honor my uncle's spirit in heaven.

106
00:06:01,199 --> 00:06:01,720
Who's there?

107
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:06,560
Geng Jing.

108
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:08,319
How dare you!

109
00:06:08,639 --> 00:06:09,720
Daring to defy your superior,

110
00:06:09,959 --> 00:06:11,079
and raise a hand against me!

111
00:06:11,959 --> 00:06:13,040
It is my duty.

112
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:18,720
You'd protect him?

113
00:06:23,439 --> 00:06:24,839
Ning Chen has yet to be tried.

114
00:06:26,519 --> 00:06:27,399
If he dies here,

115
00:06:27,959 --> 00:06:29,000
I cannot answer for it.

116
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:33,120
And what if I insist on killing him?

117
00:06:35,759 --> 00:06:36,279
As long as I stand here,

118
00:06:37,759 --> 00:06:38,639
he will not die.

119
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:42,720
Your Highness,

120
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,319
Geng Jing is highly skilled.

121
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,480
We are no match for him.

122
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:46,920
This is the Imperial Inspectorate's prison.

123
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:48,600
Trespassing here is already a grave offense.

124
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,360
If matters escalate further,

125
00:06:50,759 --> 00:06:51,680
the Empress could be implicated.

126
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:55,560
Geng Jing,

127
00:06:56,439 --> 00:06:57,800
are you certain you'd offend me

128
00:06:58,319 --> 00:06:59,480
for his sake?

129
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:02,519
Imperial Inspectorate serves His Majesty.

130
00:07:03,439 --> 00:07:04,199
Fine.

131
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,160
We shall see about this.

132
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:17,720
Are you all right?

133
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:21,439
Lord Geng, you're impressive.

134
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:23,439
Upright and unafraid of power.

135
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,399
I truly admire you.

136
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:27,079
However,

137
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:29,920
that prince is quite the fool.

138
00:07:30,399 --> 00:07:32,480
Storming the Imperial Inspectorate to kill?

139
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,240
Isn't that

140
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:37,319
twisting the tiger's tail?

141
00:07:37,839 --> 00:07:40,319
The Third Prince is the Empress's only son,

142
00:07:40,639 --> 00:07:42,160
and the Crown Prince's greatest threat.

143
00:07:43,399 --> 00:07:44,480
What a powerful background.

144
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:48,120
So the Crown Prince isn't the Empress's son?

145
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,959
As long as the position remains open,

146
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:52,199
anyone has a chance.

147
00:07:55,079 --> 00:07:55,959
It doesn't matter.

148
00:07:56,839 --> 00:07:59,360
Lord Geng, when will you sentence me?

149
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:02,399
So eager to die?

150
00:08:03,639 --> 00:08:06,800
Stuck in this sunless place every day,

151
00:08:07,279 --> 00:08:08,480
keeping company with Xiaoqiang,

152
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:10,199
I'd rather you just end it quickly.

153
00:08:16,639 --> 00:08:17,879
Who is Xiaoqiang?

154
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:22,160
Xiaoqiang isn't a person.

155
00:08:25,639 --> 00:08:27,160
And you won't be one much longer either.

156
00:08:27,839 --> 00:08:30,120
His Majesty will have you torn apart by six horses.

157
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:33,399
Six horses?

158
00:08:35,879 --> 00:08:38,000
Aren't you supposed to be exceptionally gifted?

159
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,919
The Third Prince trespassed in the Imperial Inspectorate.

160
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:06,159
His Majesty is furious.

161
00:09:06,519 --> 00:09:08,279
To protect the Third Prince, the Empress

162
00:09:08,799 --> 00:09:10,240
agreed not to pursue Ning Chen.

163
00:09:10,679 --> 00:09:11,720
But the order from above is clear,

164
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:14,159
Ning Chen must die.

165
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:16,279
Don't worry.

166
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:18,759
I have my own plans.

167
00:09:19,159 --> 00:09:21,399
There's nothing left to squeeze out of Chongzhou.

168
00:09:21,759 --> 00:09:22,720
Cut ties when we must.

169
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:24,840
But those above still need plenty of silver

170
00:09:24,879 --> 00:09:25,799
to maintain connections.

171
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:27,679
For this matter,

172
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:29,960
I trust the Left Minister will see to it.

173
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:31,879
Understood.

174
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:32,679
I take my leave.

175
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,799
Chongzhou, built up over many years,

176
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:46,720
gone just like that.

177
00:09:47,879 --> 00:09:48,759
Ning Chen!

178
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:52,360
Even grinding your bones to dust

179
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:57,440
won't quench my hatred for you!

180
00:10:00,559 --> 00:10:03,879
I'll love you even in death!

181
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:08,159
Torn by six horses is for the best!

182
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:09,679
I crossed over to this place,

183
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:11,440
The Imperial Uncle was a total disgrace,

184
00:10:11,840 --> 00:10:17,399
Only I have the most handsome face!

185
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:20,960
Not a bad life, eh?

186
00:10:21,519 --> 00:10:22,759
Wine and meat,

187
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:24,440
and a little tune too.

188
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:33,200
You big beasts, one and all,

189
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:34,240
greetings!

190
00:10:35,519 --> 00:10:37,279
It's been quite a while.

191
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:40,039
Enjoy the Imperial Inspectorate's dungeon?

192
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:43,080
Back when you were brutalizing the people,

193
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:45,120
did you ever imagine this day?

194
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:46,879
Take it back.

195
00:10:49,279 --> 00:10:49,720
Come on.

196
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,320
Throw them in.

197
00:10:52,679 --> 00:10:53,159
Open up.

198
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:01,799
Pretty spacious.

199
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:04,039
Pan Yucheng, what's the meaning of this?

200
00:11:04,679 --> 00:11:05,759
We're out of cells.

201
00:11:06,559 --> 00:11:07,600
Don't give me that nonsense.

202
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,200
The cell next to mine is empty.

203
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:09,879
So is the one across.

204
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:12,279
If I say there's none, there's none.

205
00:11:12,879 --> 00:11:14,320
What's this Pan up to?

206
00:11:15,039 --> 00:11:16,559
Locking them in with me, does he want—

207
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:21,159
Pingzi, Ah Zheng,

208
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:23,519
keep a close watch on these prisoners.

209
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:25,000
Don't let them

210
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:27,279
brawl among themselves.

211
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:28,480
Understood.

212
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:31,799
I'll love you even in death!

213
00:11:31,919 --> 00:11:32,480
Sir!

214
00:11:32,799 --> 00:11:34,320
You can't lock me up with him!

215
00:11:34,559 --> 00:11:35,440
He'll kill me!

216
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:36,200
That's right, sir!

217
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:38,039
Please move us to another cell.

218
00:11:38,159 --> 00:11:39,000
I beg you, sir!

219
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:40,360
"Brawling"

220
00:11:41,519 --> 00:11:44,759
means a private brawl.

221
00:11:49,399 --> 00:11:50,320
My esteemed lords,

222
00:11:51,799 --> 00:11:53,159
we meet again.

223
00:11:53,519 --> 00:11:54,159
Surprised?

224
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,000
Shocked?

225
00:11:57,799 --> 00:11:58,279
Oh, by the way,

226
00:11:59,519 --> 00:12:00,480
my dear lords,

227
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,200
don't you all love a good tune?

228
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:04,320
Today I'll sing one for you.

229
00:12:06,399 --> 00:12:07,279
Only thing is,

230
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:09,720
this dump has no pretty girls.

231
00:12:11,039 --> 00:12:12,679
You'll all just have to make do.

232
00:12:13,919 --> 00:12:14,960
N-Ning Chen!

233
00:12:15,399 --> 00:12:16,039
You... you...

234
00:12:16,399 --> 00:12:17,600
I haven't been tried yet.

235
00:12:17,799 --> 00:12:18,559
I haven't been convicted.

236
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:19,679
I'm still an official.

237
00:12:19,879 --> 00:12:21,480
Lay a hand on me and I'll report you!

238
00:12:23,279 --> 00:12:25,399
Lord Ai, what a comedian.

239
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:27,039
I'm already condemned to death.

240
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,480
What good would reporting me do?

241
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:30,480
Hack at my grave one more time?

242
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:33,159
This—

243
00:12:33,519 --> 00:12:34,240
These two lords—

244
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:35,519
Aren't you going to stop him?

245
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:36,840
Yes, sir!

246
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:39,879
How did I go blind?

247
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:41,399
I can't see a thing.

248
00:12:43,559 --> 00:12:44,879
Why is it so pitch dark in here?

249
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:45,600
Sir!

250
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:46,519
Old Feng!

251
00:12:46,519 --> 00:12:46,960
Old Gao, what did you say?

252
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:48,080
Old Gao! Old Feng! Old Feng!

253
00:12:48,159 --> 00:12:48,559
Sir!

254
00:12:48,679 --> 00:12:49,559
I can't see, Old Feng!

255
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:50,600
Old Gao! Old Gao!

256
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:51,240
Sir!

257
00:12:51,759 --> 00:12:52,639
Don't go, sir!

258
00:12:53,039 --> 00:12:53,960
Don't go, sir!

259
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,120
Sir!

260
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:57,519
You can't just abandon us!

261
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:59,240
Sir, come back!

262
00:13:03,759 --> 00:13:06,679
I'll love you even in death!

263
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:10,480
Torn by six horses is for the best!

264
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:12,120
Let us out, sir!

265
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:13,039
We're in here!

266
00:13:13,039 --> 00:13:13,919
He's really going to beat us to death!

267
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:14,799
Let us out!

268
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:16,879
You can't abandon us, sir!

269
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:17,960
Aren't you going to do something, sir?

270
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:18,840
Help us!

271
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:19,840
Take this!

272
00:13:30,039 --> 00:13:31,279
Spare me! Spare me!

273
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:37,960
You all know how to sing it now?

274
00:13:38,759 --> 00:13:40,360
Yes, yes, yes!

275
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:46,200
I'll love you even in death!

276
00:13:46,759 --> 00:13:50,600
Torn by six horses is for the best!

277
00:13:52,679 --> 00:13:54,159
I crossed over to this place,

278
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:58,000
The Imperial Uncle was a total disgrace,

279
00:13:58,799 --> 00:14:02,159
Only you have the most handsome face!

280
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:05,159
Not bad.

281
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:08,159
Old Feng.

282
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:09,879
Take Ning Chen away.

283
00:14:10,039 --> 00:14:10,519
Yes, sir.

284
00:14:12,919 --> 00:14:13,320
Move.

285
00:14:13,759 --> 00:14:14,159
Hey, wait.

286
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:15,279
What's that supposed to mean, Old Feng?

287
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,080
The prisoner has been brought in.

288
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:20,279
Brothers!

289
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:21,360
Hard at work, huh?

290
00:14:22,039 --> 00:14:22,840
Look how late it is.

291
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:23,919
And you're still here pulling overtime.

292
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:25,720
Look at my poor brother here, so tired

293
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:26,919
he can barely keep his eyes open.

294
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:28,440
Yet still standing so straight and proper.

295
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:30,679
Still as cold and aloof as ever.

296
00:14:32,159 --> 00:14:34,799
Why's your rope still this long?

297
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:40,799
Been hitting the bottle hard again lately?

298
00:14:40,919 --> 00:14:42,080
Your beer belly's back, huh?

299
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:45,000
Why work at this hour anyway?

300
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:46,159
There's no overtime pay.

301
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:48,480
Why hang around this godforsaken place?

302
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:50,120
Go get a late-night snack,

303
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:51,399
have some drinks,

304
00:14:51,519 --> 00:14:53,639
hit up the entertainment quarters.

305
00:14:55,159 --> 00:14:56,480
Smooth-talking little punk.

306
00:14:56,720 --> 00:14:57,919
Watch your attitude.

307
00:14:58,440 --> 00:14:59,879
Take a good look at where you are.

308
00:15:01,279 --> 00:15:02,000
Where is this?

309
00:15:03,039 --> 00:15:04,320
Isn't this just the Imperial Inspectorate?

310
00:15:05,279 --> 00:15:06,440
What kind of attitude do I need?

311
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:08,320
My attitude

312
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:13,279
is to look out for my brothers' 9-to-5.

313
00:15:14,279 --> 00:15:15,919
Still running your mouth?

314
00:15:16,639 --> 00:15:17,240
Guards!

315
00:15:18,039 --> 00:15:19,039
Take him down.

316
00:15:23,519 --> 00:15:24,720
Pan Yucheng, you're serious about this?

317
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:25,919
What did you expect?

318
00:15:26,519 --> 00:15:27,120
Chenzi.

319
00:15:29,399 --> 00:15:30,159
This is bad.

320
00:15:32,919 --> 00:15:33,639
Apply the torture.

